<DOC><DOCNO> AP880928-0206 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-28-88 2131EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Germany-Escape     09-28 0212</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Germany-Escape,0218</SECOND><HEAD>Border Guards Fire on Two Men Fleeing to West</HEAD><DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Communist East German border guards shot at twomen who scaled the Berlin Wall to flee to the West on Wednesday,and they arrested a woman accompanying the men, police said.   The men escaped uninjured into West Berlin, said a West Berlinpolice spokesman who spoke on condition of anonymity.   Police said the woman was arrested by the East Berlin guardsafter she fell while running and hurt herself.   The incident came two days after the three allied powers in WestBerlin issued a protest note condemning the use of force inpreventing an escape attempt Sunday night.   In another incident, East Berlin border guards fired warningshots Sunday night to stop two men racing to scale theheavily-fortified wall that divides the city. They were arrested,but police said they were not injured.   In Monday's protest note, signed by the United States, Franceand Britain, the allies condemned the shooting as a ``violation ofbasic human rights'' and an ``affront against the values ofcivilized society.''   The West German government and the West Berlin Senateimmediately condemned Wednesday's incident.   More than 322 people people have fled East Germany to WestBerlin or West Germany this year.</TEXT></DOC>